  "english_translation": {
    "entry_translation": "Sūrat al-Anfāl.\n\nMedinan. Its counterpart (naẓīrah) in the two Madani counts is Sūrat al-Ḥajj; in the Kufi count, Sūrat al-Zumar; and in the Shami count, Sūrat al-Furqān. It has no counterpart in the Makki and Basri counts.\n\nIts words are one thousand two hundred and thirty-one, and its letters are five thousand two hundred and ninety-four. It is seventy-five verses in the Kufi count; seventy-six in the two Madani counts, the Makki, and the Basri; and seventy-seven in the Shami count.\n\nIts points of disagreement are three verse-endings: “thumma yughlabūn” is counted by the Basri and the Shami and not counted by the others; “li-yaqḍiya llāhu amran kāna mafʿūlan” is not counted by the Kufi and is counted by the others; and “bi-naṣrihi wa-bi-l-muʾminīn” is not counted by the Basri and is counted by the others.\n\nIn it there are, by consensus, eight places that resemble verse-endings without being counted: “ulāʾika humu l-muʾminūn”; “rijza l-shayṭān”; “fawqa l-aʿnāq”; “ʿani l-masjidi l-ḥarām”; “illā l-muttaqūn”; “yawma l-furqān”; “yawma l-taqā l-jamʿān”; and the second occurrence of “amran kāna mafʿūlan,” namely the one after which comes “wa-ilā llāhi turjaʿu l-umūr.”",
    "ruus_translation_note": "The transmitted رؤوس الآي are complete enough to recover a full later-Madani 76-head sequence, but the witness’s displayed numerals are not a stable independent ordinal layer. The first head “مؤمنين” is unnumbered; after displayed 41 “مفعولا,” the expected next display numeral is omitted on an unnumbered “عليم”; the witness then resumes at displayed 42 “الصدور” and ends with a blank display-total line “٧٥”. The structured ordinals below therefore give the authoritative recovered sequence, while display_number_in_witness preserves the witness behavior."
  },
